1.

Requirement:
“System shall generate a monthly accounts payable report including total outstanding balance and number of unpaid invoices.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“monthly”

Why:

It’s unclear whether the report is generated at the end of the month, the beginning, or on-demand for a given month.
2.

Requirement:
“System shall allow authorized users to approve invoices exceeding $5,000 before payment is issued.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“authorized users”

Why:

The requirement doesn’t define which roles are considered authorized, so access control rules are incomplete.
3.

Requirement:
“System shall store vendor records including vendor ID, name, address, and contact number.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“address”

Why:

It does not specify the structure of the address (e.g., required fields like city or ZIP code), leaving room for inconsistent data entry.
4.

Requirement:
“System shall validate invoice submissions by checking for duplicate invoice numbers and missing required fields.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“required fields”

Why:

The requirement does not list which fields are required, so developers may implement different validation rules.
5.

Requirement:
“System shall allow users to search invoices by vendor name and invoice date.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“invoice date”

Why:

It’s unclear whether this refers to the issue date, due date, or entry date.
6.

Requirement:
“System shall retain payment transaction records for a minimum of five years.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“retain”

Why:

It’s not clear whether records must remain actively accessible or can be archived after a certain period.
7.

Requirement:
“System shall send email notifications to users when an invoice becomes overdue.”

Ambiguity (Unambiguity):

“becomes overdue”

Why:

The exact trigger point (e.g., immediately after due date vs. after a grace period) is not defined.
8.

Requirement:
“System shall allow users to update vendor contact information while maintaining an audit log of changes.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“audit log”

Why:

It does not specify what details must be recorded in the log (e.g., timestamp, user ID, old vs. new values).
9.

Requirement:
“System shall export financial reports in CSV and PDF formats.”

Ambiguity (Meaningfulness):

“financial reports”

Why:

It’s unclear which specific reports are included, so the scope of export functionality is not fully defined.
10.

Requirement:
“System shall restrict access to payment data based on predefined user roles and permissions.”

Ambiguity (Completeness):

“predefined user roles and permissions”

Why:

The requirement does not specify what those roles and permissions are, leaving implementation details incomplete.
